==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Pellicle
<hw>Pel"li*cle</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>pellicula</ets>, dim. of <ets>pellis</ets> skin: cf. F.
<ets>pellicule</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A thin skin or
film.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>A thin film formed on the surface
of an evaporating solution.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Pellicular</ent>⟦br⟧
